constant contemplation and self-c=
orrection can be reduced to a quick delusional
jump to the end". Unless one=
 catches it whenever something transient and perishable is drawing one's at=
tention, one will not overcome each such instinct. Until each such instinct=
 is overcome, "all is imperishable Self" is just a theory one is repeating =
like a parrot. The covering/eclipse/bondage is quite real until then.
