Unfortunately, some assertions of Jnana Yoga an=
d Adwaita Vedanta can be misleading. I will try to explain it with a nice a=
nalogy from physics.
=C2=A0
This world is made up of different objects. The=
y are made up of molecules with a lot of vacuum in between them. Molecules =
are made up of atoms and a lot of vacuum in between them. Atoms are made up=
 of electrons, protons etc and a lot of vacuum in between them. Even those =
particles are made up of smaller particles and a lot of vacuum in between t=
hem. As you keep dividing, you will see that things are made up of subtle p=
ortions of matter and a lot of vacuum. When you go to the level of small pa=
rticles, work by physicists such as Heisenberg, Broglie, Schroedinger etc s=
ays that you can't even observe and determine the properties of those parti=
cles confidently without affecting them. They may not even exist as "matter=
" with specific location and momentum or even as waves, independent of the =
observer.
=C2=A0
However, despite that "quantum mechanics" reality at the s=
ubtlest level, we have normal "mechanics" too. A lot of gross objects made =
up of=C2=A0 those subtle particles are gross enough and obey some grosser l=
aws of physics (e.g. Newton's laws). We can find their positions, momentum =
etc accurately and make them move deterministically.
=C2=A0
When one is des=
igning a car or a pulley system or a rocket, one can leave quantum mechanic=
s and use normal mechanics. However, when one is doing research on bosons e=
tc, one must pay attention to quantum mechanics. Otherwise, one will commit=
 errors.
=C2=A0
Similarly, at the subtlest level, Self alone exists. Things=
 that seem to exist may not even exist independent of the observer. However=
, there are also the laws of karma that govern the grosser reality (body, h=
ealth, job, spouse, children, house, car, money etc). Rishis taught Adwaita=
 Vedanta and also the laws that govern the world of duality (e.g. the law o=
f karma).
=C2=A0
When one's awareness focuses on gross objects and one is w=
orking with the gross world, one better leave "quantum spirituality" (Adwai=
ta Vedanta) and focus on normal spirituality. However, when one's awareness=
 becomes very subtle and one starts to deal with mystical experiences, deit=
ies etc, one must pay attention to Adwaita Vedanta. Otherwise, one will com=
mit errors!!
